# PDR-019 U4 / ADR-040 D6 — naming enforcement in the bootstrap script
# (owner: shopsystem-templates; request_bugfix — tightens the existing but
# unpinned naming behavior, extends the ADR-038 BC-name gate lead-xntx under
# the derived <product>). Only the ONE user-chosen lead repo name needs the
# validate -> derive -> offer-rename path; every other repo is tooling-created
# under the derived <product>, so the shape is forced for free. The literal
# "acme" is an illustrative product slug, not a fixed contract value.
@scenario_hash:2f9f7bab6fb3e36f
Scenario: a lead repo name matching the *-lead shape is accepted and its product slug is derived into the manifest
  Given the forked lead repository is named "acme-lead"
  When the bootstrap script validates the repository name
  Then it accepts the name as matching the "*-lead" shape
  And it derives the product slug "acme" by stripping the "-lead" suffix
  And it writes "product: acme" into the manifest as the declared product identity

@scenario_hash:7c6797430afa1749
Scenario: a lead repo name not matching the *-lead shape is offered a gh repo rename rather than a re-fork
  Given the forked lead repository is named "acme" which does not match the "*-lead" shape
  When the bootstrap script validates the repository name
  Then it reports the name does not match the "*-lead" shape
  And it offers to run "gh repo rename" to rename the existing repository to "acme-lead" in place
  And it does not require the human to re-fork the starter template

@scenario_hash:db2131f49c170bc8
Scenario: every tooling-created repository is forced under the derived product slug
  Given the bootstrap script has derived the product slug "acme"
  When the script creates the beads repository and any BC repository for the product
  Then the beads repository is named "acme-lead-beads"
  And any BC repository named "<bc>" is created as "acme-<bc>" with its beads repository "acme-<bc>-beads"
  And no tooling-created repository can be named outside the "acme-*" shape
